	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Bard Epic Change</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=578829" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abm.asp?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
  <p>Agrath writes:</p>
  <blockquote><font color=beige>
    <p>As of the 6/6/2002 patch, <a href="http://www.everlore.com/items/items.asp?mode=show&IID=49837" target=blank>The White dragon Scale Cloak</a> no longer needs the white scale from Lady Vox, but 
    instead uses a White Dragon Hide. Verant says that the since the scale is no longer 
    used in the quest, this allows Bards the chance to get their epic without competition with spell casters looking for a cloak.</p>
  </blockquote></font>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
