	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This post is just a tangent off of the bard epic patch so if you're looking for info on that subject don't continue reading.<BR>
<BR>
I must say that I'm pleasantly shocked to see Verant making an epic quest change.  I can't help but feel optimistic about a /petition to get the monk quest tweaked a little.  This &quot;is&quot; a whine so go with me on this one, I believe I have a valid complaint.  I must first point out that many a monk before me have completed their epic and this isn't to discredit their oustanding efforts in anyway so flame me as you will.  Currently my level 50 monk is camping the Raster of Guk.  I should enlighten all those who don't know about this very rare spawn.  Supposedly Raster has a 5% spawn chance as compared to 10% froglok and 85% greater minotaur.  With that said it's easy to find posts new and old about horror stories where fellow monks have camped Raster for more than 200 real life hours.  You'll also find the lucky saps who claim to have gotten him in less than 10.  Now, add that to the fact that you'll be competing for the camp with untold numbers of other monks looking to get their epic component.  Recently I spent a day logging on and off &quot;sharing&quot; the camp with a new monk friend.  This person camped Raster for 14 straight hours following the Raster guide from monkly-business.com.  I picked up where he left off for 3 more hours.  In total he and I saw 36 ph's.  Not one Raster.  Tell me...does this sound logical?  5%= 1/20...we saw nearly 40. Granted, getting a raid together to kill a dragon for an epic piece is no small feat especially when other people need the same item for their epic or items etc.  But I'd love to have a chance at a guaranteed spawn that all I needed to do was roll on the Idol of Zan Fi. Keep in mind that Raster drops a piece for the first of 2 robes needed, and there are 5 different encounters with high level mobs to kill after that, which all require a large group of people to kill.  Again, tell me...does this sound logical?  It's excessive in my opinion.  I'm not looking for Verant to change anything with the epic quest because I personally feel that it's creative, rich in content and very challenging.  The perfect recipe for a sense of accomplishment and pride once you actually earn your epic.  I'm just looking for Verant to ease the pain on this impossible camp all we monks have grown to hate.  A good point I might add, it has driven many monks in nice guilds to kill Brother Zephyl in RM who drops the Robe of the Lost Circle (nerfed I know, but he still drops it at a lesser rate).  The fact that Verant nerfed Zeph's drop rate has to set off alarms somewhere that this camp is overkill to say the least.  I mean people have organized raids to kill this level 60 NPC to bypass Raster.  I'm beating a dead horse here but hopefully everyone get's my point.<BR>
I wub j00 Raster....NOW POP ALREADY!<BR>
<BR>
Rokjaw Preechurfysts<BR>
50 Human Monk<BR>
Saryrn Server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
